MatrixEQTL Primary Results

Significant Hits, FDR < 0.05

Check the number of found eQTLs, unique CpGs and SNPs in all datasets.

cbPalette <- c("#0072B2", "#009E73", "#E69F00", "#F0E442", "#D55E00", "#CC79A7", "#56B4E9", "#999999")

sign.hits.df %>%
    as.matrix() %>%
    reshape2::melt(var.names = c("ID", "Treatment"), value.name = "cnt") %>%
    ggplot(aes(y = cnt, x = Var2, fill = as.factor(as.numeric(Var2)))) + geom_col() + geom_text(aes(label = comma(cnt,
    accuracy = 1L), y = cnt), stat = "identity", vjust = -0.2, size = 2.5) + scale_y_continuous(labels = scientific) +
    # scale_fill_viridis(discrete = TRUE, alpha = 0.9, option = 'C') +
labs(title = " ", y = "Count", x = " ") + facet_wrap(~Var1, ncol = 3) + theme(legend.position = "none",
    legend.title = element_blank(), panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank(),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 10), axis.title = element_text(size = 8), axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = cbPalette)

plot.title <- paste0("Independent and significant at FDR <= ", fdr.thr, " QTMs.", "\nResult of MatrixEQTL")
GetScatterPlot2(all.full.df, plot.title = plot.title, fdr.thr = fdr.thr)

Upset plots

eQTM level

library(UpSetR)

eqtms <- list(delta = all.full.df[treatment == "delta", eQTM_ID], dex = all.full.df[treatment == "dex",
    eQTM_ID], veh = all.full.df[treatment == "veh", eQTM_ID])

upset(fromList(eqtms), sets = c("delta", "dex", "veh"), nsets = 3, nintersects = 20, mainbar.y.label = "Number of intersections, eQTM",
    text.scale = 1, keep.order = T, sets.bar.color = c("#0072B2", "#009E73", "#E69F00"), order.by = "freq")
